,Recommended,286160,29133559,Posted: 8 January,all,Neo,"Being a fan of board games/tabletop gaming, I stumbled across Tabletop Simulator some time ago as a means of playing Eldritch Horror through one of the projects in the workshop. Not only did the TS version cut down on setup/dismantle time, it happened to be a functional and more convenient way to play the game, even with people over distances. One of the most magical parts about board gaming is that you are face-to-face with the other players and get to interact with them in person while you're playing the game. Unfortunately, given our busy schedules and the distances between us, we are not always able to meet in person and lay out our games on common table. TS gives people a chance to play board games virtually, conveniently, and practically, wherever they may be, and cuts down on the prep time which makes these games more accessible to us board game enthusiasts. In addition, TS also has just about every single board game out there available for download on the workshop or as top-quality DLC from the steam store. Without further ado, here's to many more hours of tabletop gaming to look forward to! And to be clear, I fully recommend this game if you're into board games!!!"
