,Recommended,286160,31712178,Posted: 12 May,all,thöjtt.kriime.org/lol,"This game is great if you are a hobby gamer. If you don't have it and you're a hobby gamer that is ridiculous. Why wouldn't you want to indoctrinate all your online friends into the elite ranks of hobby gamers. Why wouldn't you want to play any game in your physical library (via workshop mods) with literally seconds of load time and setup (with scripted setup mods).This game is an easy buy even at full price. I have played a few games of Dead of winter with a close friend who playing tabletop with is impractical due to distance. Solo Eldritch horror with no setup breakdown thanks to scripts has made the game playable for me on weeknights when I don't have the time to whip out the full set and set it all up. Save function is a lifesaver as well.The controls are a little fiddly but managable. The backgrounds... the setting you are playing in is notably ridiculous: alleys, meadows, stupid places that games would never be played in.Just having a workshop full of any hobby game you can dream of is worth 10x the sticker price for this game. You can playtest anything before buying it. Disclaimer: not anything, most things. Descent second edition seems to be a hard one to find a good workshop upload. Miniature games are harder to scan I am sure.I really enjoy just opening up games and messing around with the components. I definitely prefer learning games with a physical copy. I find it incredibly fiddly to learn games on here. The tablet for rules could use some improvement. I can't get PDFs from google to open properly. Having like a television sized object that has it's own PDF viewer or chrome built in would be insanely useful. Rules appear so small, and it kind of sucks. Being able to upload PDFs into the notes could solve this problem too. I hate opening a game and seeing a bunch of links for rules and youtube vids.The DLC is pretty worthless. There are 2 games on there I am slightly interested in and I have the same issue learning those as any other game on TTS. I need a physical copy of sycthe and Zombicide if I am going to play and teach on TTS.Overall this game, with it's flaws and room for growth is an obvious buy if you are a table top gamer. Don't be stupid. Just buy it. This game is perfect for hobby gamers, even if you don't really play videogames. If you are a hobby gamer and only have 1 game in your steam library this should be it. Buy it. Play it. Now."
