,Recommended,286160,14226499,"Posted: 29 January, 2015",all,Silhouette,"Do not discount this game as a simple board game sim; Believe me when I say it has surprised me time and time again.Tabletop Simulator is a fantastic party game, the ideal solution to anyone who has ever wanted be able to play that one board game with all of their distant friends, or even those nearby without the ridiculous mess that usually goes into them.This game comes with a standard pack of classical tabletop games, such as Checkers, Chess, Mahjongg, and even some RPG tools in case you want to play old-school miniatures. That, however, is not where this game shines. Its true worth is the fact that Workshop Integration and an active modding community allows you to play almost any tabletop game imaginable, from Cards against Humanity to Pokemon Master Trainer to Munchkin to Liar's Dice to Sellswords to Triple Triad. Given time, almost any game, no matter how obscure or how niche, will find its way to the Workshop and therefore be playable for you and up to eight friends.PROS:-a large amount of agency is afforded to players in order to provide an optimal game experience-an almost limitless library of modules is available via the workshop, giving access to hundreds of distinct games-a tutorial explains most of the obscure commands and keys fairly effectivelyCONS:-some functions that one might expect aren't available (no way to import backgrounds independent of game-types, some kind of inventory functions for players for items other than cards, etc.)Ultimately, the game is absolutely worth it if you and yours have ever wanted to play a particular tabletop game without all the hassle of having to be cluttered around a messy game board or table. I absolutely recommend this game and its various workshop modules."
