,Recommended,286160,33382017,Posted: 8 July,all,Bran,"Welcome to my review of Tabletop SimulatorWhat is Tabletop Simulator?Tabletop Simulator is a game based on simulating tabletop games such as Uno, Monopoly, Skip Bo, Candyland, Apples To Apples etc. The premess of the game itself is so simple, but its what the community did to this game that made is so beautiful.My Personal Experience With The GameThis game has been one that I have loved so much, even though its so basic in nature compared to the other games that I play on a daily basis. During the 2017 Steam Summer Sale I went ahead and bought a 4 pack for 30 dollars, and it was well worth it. The next day on of the best moments of this game happened, and it made me instantly fall in love. Me and someone I just met off of some of my other friends wanted to play, and I did too, and I thought Monopoly, and he said yeah. After that, we played for 4 hours straight, laughing, having a good time, getting to know each other, and by the end of those 4 hours I felt like iv'e known him for the longest time, it was a great bonding expereince, and it was thanks to Tabletop Simulator. There will also be nights where there will be 4 or 5 of us wanting to play a card game and a have a good time. Many times yelling at each other playing Uno, or laughing playing Apples and Apples. Stragitizing playing Skip Bo, or spending hours trying to find waldo in 4 boards, theres been many of times in this game where it was fun, and it felt really real, even though we were just on a computer screen, this is why I love this game. But one thing about this game finally made me love it so much, and its the simplest thing, but it's so amazing. Puzzles. After I go to work and come back at almost 10:00 at night, I boot up my Indie Alternative playlist, find my favorite picture of nature, and spend 2 hours putting together the 140 peice puzzle, the whole world around me just stops, except for my playlist, and the puzzle, and it's the best thing ever, nothing has ever felt so relaxing before, and it's so great, this is why I love Tabletop Simulator. It can be a bonding expereince, a social get together, or on the of the most realaxing moemnts of your day, and this is why it's one of the most amazing games out there.Final ThoughtsThis game is amazing, it's everything I wanted out of 30$, the graphics are great, the audio is great, the immersion is there, it's a great game, and it's worth it if you:Enjoy doing things such as puzzles.Want to have a virtual cardgame session with your friends at 1:00 in the morning.Want to yell at each other over eels and escolatorsWant to draw D***KS all over the Candyland people and laugh for minutes.Want to enjoy your friends company in one of the most timeless methods.With these thoughts, I think that Tabletop Simulator grabs a 9.5/10. I love it, but it's not 10/10 because its notperfect.Thank you for reading."
