,Recommended,286160,9866546,"Posted: 18 April, 2014",all,Mark-12,"The Good:  I've only mucked about on this for about 10 minutes so far, and yes, this IS an Early Access game, but so far, I see this as a WONDERFUL tool for table top gamers (board games, RPG's, miniatures, etc).  From what I've seen on the Forums, the Devs are going to update content (a tape measure is one of the ones they've talked about...for miniature gaming), so this is going to add even more variation to the creation and game play.  I love the physics involved in the game, things like picking up and moving the pieces, shuffling cards, rolling dice, and even flipping the table (yes...that flipping the table).The Bad:  It's Early Access...it's effectively a beta...so right now, you pretty much have the basic stuff in the game.  There is a thread on the Forums regarding the use of copyrighted material...this can hamper some of the more popular ""games"" being reproduced.The Ugly:  The ""game room"" is...well...empty...there's the table...but no walls, no floor...just the table (this is something that is added later).That's really it...I enjoy the games so far, I hope that more is added in and that copyright holders allow for their products to be added to the Steam Workshop (when that's added)."
