,Recommended,286160,11932058,"Posted: 31 August, 2014",all,rewalzzz,"There are without a doubt some people that are going to find Tabletop Simulator (we'll call it TS for short) not worth the $14.99 dollar price tag. There are going to be people who think that it would be a much better idea to go on a website like Pogo and play the games you might enjoy on TS for free. I can't blame them for thinking that. I, however, am not one of those people, and think this simulator is absolutely great if you have friends to play it with.In TS you are given the freedom to play however you want to play. There are no rules in TS. You could even make your own game and it would not matter, because in TS there are no rules at all. Seven card stud? No problem. Your own twist on Monopoly? Go ahead.If you do not have anyone to play this game with, at the moment, I cannot reccomend it. You can join servers put up with the server browser, but these games are usually unorganized, and they do not have voice chat. If you want to get your money's worth for this game, get four of your friends together and have an awesome game of Cards Against Humanity or Poker.The Steam Workshop really adds a whole lot to this game. It insures that there will never be a lack of content, (as long as the community stays active.)At the end of the day, some will find it hard to justify spending money on something they could do to less of an extent (yet an awesome one at that) for free. At the end of the day, it really depends on what you think. If you consider buying it, consider persuading a friend."
