76561198029300088,Recommended,286160,30780702,Posted: 27 March,all,yenkin2001,"First and foremost this is a simulator of a table top, there is no AI, can you play solo yes and many of the board games allow for solo play especially co-op games.  In most cases you need to know the rules, the games often don't have rules with them. Most cases just go download a PDF of the rules, they are out there  on the internet somewhere, and in some cases the mod developers will put the link in the game.If you are expecting the game to do the work for you, not going to happen, you are in control, if you are lucky someone has scripted a few things but for the most part it is like walking up to the table, setting up the game to some degree and playing.  I love the coop games, and have played a couple that I own using this simulator and I am quite pleased with the way it works.  They are great for practice runs of games as you try to learn the rules.  So far I have tried Pandemic: Cthulhu version, Arkahm Horror the Card Game, One Deck Dungeon, and just set up Arkham Horror the Core game.IF you like the games, then you are encourage to go out and buy a physical copy of the game, in some cases not as easy as it sounds.  Final Fantasy, has a lot of games that are waiting to be shipped, reprinted and sadly in some cases are no longer in print.  But Board Game Geek market can be your friend.I do admit that I find the interface clunky at times, as you have to often bring up cards to see them (Easy using Alt).  But heck with my eye sight I have to bring cards up to read them anyway, so as stated you get a table top feel for the games.  Like in real life, things fall over,  you can even flip the who board if you want.  Thankfully it has a recall last using a back arrow, then it just sets up from the last position of the game.9/10 I think on this one.  Play Games here, buy games and support your local game store.  The interface also has built in hosting and I believe chat too.  So you can host a game with your friends."
