76561198225098124,Recommended,286160,31457107,Posted: 30 April,all,Lord Ignus,"If you are someone who loves board games, the worth of Tabletop Simulator cannot be overstated.Fancy a game of chess or cards a tabletop RPG with your friend, but he's in another state? No problem: just jump on Tabletop Simulator, and play together on a virtual board with pieces, cards, and dice to move around. Not only are there several games that come standard with your purchase, but the community on Steam Workshop have crafted just about every game you can think of: I've even found a mod of Heroscape!It should be noted (upon reading some negative reviews) that this is a merely a physics-based sandbox: it will not carry out game-related actions for you, nor will you be able to play against AI opponents. Any physical action you would have to make in a real board game, you would have to make here. However, this actually works to the game's advantage: without the need to program game rules (though there are some mods that can perform various scripts), modding becomes much easier, and the number of games available becomes virtually limitless."
