,Recommended,286160,21548826,"Posted: 29 February, 2016",all,Good Versus Evil,"This is the game that Steam Workshop is made for.  The community surrounding this game is absolutely amazing and it is rare to find a game that hasn't been ported into this format.  Some work better than others (Timed games like Escape are a bit difficult without getting very familiar with the control system), but overall the quality of what's out there is very very solid.I did have a tough time getting used to the controls at first, but they become intuitive after a bit of practice.  I would recommend watching a video of a game first before attempting to play it in here, I think it makes it easier to pick up personally.My recommendations are Secret Hitler (or Palpatine) and DungeonQuest (A personal favorite of mine outside of the simulator, somehow made easier to play virtually).This game is worth the purchase, even at full price."
