,Recommended,286160,14069023,"Posted: 19 January, 2015",all,Krozber,"As far as open-ended gameplay is concerned, I can't imagine a game that can beat Tabletop Simulator (TS). All manner of card games, board games, strategy games, and pen and paper games can be played using this ""game."" It also comes preloaded with many classic board games like checkers, chess, backgammon, and many more. What's going to make TS unbeatable is the ability to load steam workshop content. Just about any game that you play on a table can be modeled and uploaded for everyone to use (barring copyright infringement). This allows you to, say, play your Dungeons and Dragons campaign with highly-detailed customized models and scenery with your friends around the country. The possibilities are endless! Furthermore, this game is still in early-access! I can't even believe that it's just going to get better and better as time goes on! I've already purchased five copies of this game for me and my friends, and I recommend that you pick up a copy as well."
