,Recommended,286160,13190773,"Posted: 1 December, 2014",all,Kenny,"This is a fantastic game that you can virtually play any card game or board game with your friends. It is very well developed and it is quite stable despite being in deveopment stage.Now if you are wondering how it works, thats how it works for card games:You basically pick a colour on the table. You get cards. Cards can be dealed by someone or they can also be auto-dealed. There is an area in the table that belongs to you. When you put the cards there or around there, it is not visible to others but to you only. also no body can see a card if it is flip down. You can freely flip cards. put the cards in the middle etc. So it is quite simple to play.Here is a list of what you can do with the game:-Play the games that comes with the original game:-all card games that require a regular deck as you can get as many decks as you want,-many board games including chess, backgammon, checkers, chinese checkers...-all dice games, including FRP die-Play many FRP games, with additional help from DLCs you can even create character sheets easily or create your own maps and corridors...-FRP characters and creastures have nice animation and they can also move attack or die...-Play virtually any card, board, die, FRP game, thanks to the DLCs. (I have personally found a rare and wonderful game called Skipbo)-Customise the game table, background, etc.-Its also possible to play some games as hotseat but this needs improvements.Negative sides:-Customization of the game table and background are somewhat limited for basic users.-There is no AI, or computer players as it is against the nature of this simulation. So you cannot play a game that is normally multiplayer (like many card games) by yourself. Nevertheless, you can still play solitare games and any other games that you would play by yourself (perhaps chess, though I find it a little sad to play it alone)- In the multiplayer game rooms, if you host the game and if you have not made sure that  you locked some features and limited power with yourself and right people then some guys may come and flip your table, mess with your cards or mess with your game. Some strangers in multiplayer rooms act like a three years old babies. Nevertheless it is also possible to find some serious gamers as well.-Hotseat feature is not fully implemented. It is just a possibility I see."
