,Recommended,286160,12491032,"Posted: 14 October, 2014",all,E3kHatena,"Tabletop Simulator is a bit confused as to whether it wants to be like Surgeon Simulator or be more realistic, and really that's a little bit of a problem. The controls are built for the mouse/keyboard, but the virtual hand is finicky and has a tendency to knock stuff about, making more complex games (like the tabletop RPG) more difficult to play as a result. However, with the workshop, it is easy to find dozens of different games to play, ranging from new, old, classic and infamous games. It takes little time to set up and is a lot of fun with friends, but poor controls make it a bit of a challenge to play some games. I'd reccomend it, but just take your time and remember, there's an undo button in case Jerry throws (his pawn/your pawn/the entire table) away."
