76561198008900293,Recommended,286160,13000926,"Posted: 18 November, 2014",all,Jasper,"I highly recommend this game if you like board games. If you don't like board games, well this could probably help you get into them! Card games are also included in this as well. It's not a joke simulator either. It's super serious and is also not ""table-flip simulator"" as some of my friends have called it. Yes you can flip the table and it's hilarious, but it's not the main point of the game. You can create your own custom games as well and with workshop support the possibilities are endless. There's even online multiplayer, so you can play with their friends. As far as how resource intensive it is on the computer, I have a bit of a bad computer, but I can run this game very smoothly on ultra (Windows 7 32 bit, Nvidia GEforce 550, 4GB ram, 3.1 GHz processor, and not to mention a very slow read and write speed for the hard drive) and I have been able to spam objects onto the table quite a bit before lagging, though I have to run it on very high in order to play cards against humanity from the workshop. The game still looks great on the lower graphics settings as well. Since it's still early access, I imagine the optimization will only get better as well as all the features.There's also a short tutorial and you can hit the ? key on your keyboard to bring up controls. There's also controller support, which is odd for a game like this, but hey, whatever floats your boat, I guess."
