,Recommended,286160,16037944,"Posted: 28 May, 2015",all,MurrayL,"Tabletop Simulator is a versatile and easy-to-use set of tools with which you can play almost any traditional board game, card game, or RPG. Many existing games are available on the Steam Workshop (although copyright claims often remove more well-known titles), but you can also import your own graphics, so if you want to play Obscure Game: The Rare Expansion, you can scan the bits in and play it in Tabletop Simulator with very little effort.The multiplayer works well, and has lots of neat features to help out with things like fog of war, picking up multiple objects, drawing diagrams, and writing notes.This game does not include pre-made rules for chess, or anything else of the sort. It's a game that simulates a tabletop, and the game bits you choose to put on that tabletop, with physics and some 'convenience' features. If you want a game that will handle rules automatically, you're missing the point and should look elsewhere.Incredibly well-supported by the developers, Tabletop Simulator seems to get an update every couple of weeks with great new features. It's very encouraging to see such active development."
