,Recommended,286160,20275734,"Posted: 3 January, 2016",all,boiling water,"My first review was a little shallow, here's a more in depth one:Tabletop Simulator is a game where you can select board games to play with your friends. Yes, there is DLC, but there is also Steam Workshop support, which is better than DLC (when it comes to this game). You can make games, you can play those games, you can script those games... etc. Not to mention what other people ALREADY made on the workshop. If a board game exists, it's on the workshop. Tabletop Simulator is just $20 for every board game in the world. ""But I can play all these games online for free!"" ... no you can't. Don't talk to me about that BS. Listen, this is actually MORE than just board games. It's a real table that simulates physics and you can make your own models or use other models. I'm barely scratching the surface. I made some good friends on this game. Definitely reccomended if you love board games or having a guy's night out without getting out of your chair."
