,Recommended,286160,9901149,"Posted: 22 April, 2014",all,nic,"Tabletop Simulator is one of the greatest things to come to gaming in a LONG time. Play any boardgame imaginable, you're not just confined to the 15 game modes the devs give you. With mods you can literally play any boardgame. The mods are pretty small in download size too, 5kb for a monopoly mod I found. This game is soon to have steam workshop too, so everything you could ever want to play will be in one central hub.This is of course a multiplayer game. You can seemlessly drop in and out of any of the listed servers, provided they arent locked with a password. If the host has a game loaded such as monopoly people can still join and play without having to download the mod. Hosting your own server is also very easy, theres no extra download for it, and you dont have to port forward or use hamachi. When hosting, you will run into people who will flip the table. Fortunately there is a back button to undo any mess a person may have made, and a kick/ban button to prevent any further mishap.If you want to be able to play any board/card/tabletop rpg game with anyone at any time, then Tabletop Simulator is definately for you."
