,Not Recommended,286160,13548358,"Posted: 23 December, 2014",all,JJledzep,"I have played around with it for about two hours now and there is one reason I am not recommending this. It says on the store page it has single player.IT DOES NOT!There is no AI or any kind of virtual opponent. There's also no rule system governing the games. If I had known that (like not having ""Single Player"" on the store page) I would not have bought this. Now you are at the mercy of fair play with people online.So the game in itself is very good, it has some graphical issues and the control is difficult sometimes, but it has a lot of potential. I just feel I wasted my money because there is no single player component. Unless you want to count playing solitaire without any rule system. It's basically just a sandbox with nice physics. If you're looking for that, go buy it. If you're looking to play some boardgames without worrying about rules and/or finding opponents online, this is not for you.Edit: Incredible how all positive reviews on this game are helpful and the negative ones are not."
