76561198041493817,Not Recommended,286160,31444099,Posted: 29 April,all,Annoyingnome,"I bought this game with no idea how horrible the controls would be. Sure, the idea of playing board games worth £100s was too tantalizing to pass up. But what they don't tell you is that the usability is so horrid it makes the experience of playing a board game three times as hard as it normally is - the exact opposite of what you'd expect from a computer game.If you're thinking of buying this game, it is probably worth checking out a youtube video or two to see how it all works. Consider that in your typical board game you will need to read the rules, set up the components, deal cards, chuck dice, etc. When playing a well-designed board game app, however, all this fiddleness is removed - you might simply click on a button to simulate a die roll or click on a deck to receive your card. It usually cuts the play time down to less than half. Pretty neat, right?But TTS does the exact opposite of the above. No game is already set out neatly for you. There are no rules to let you know how to play a particular game you've never tried before. Each card has to picked up by 'hand' (dragging the mouse), and each die the same. While some veterans users may argue that it allows you to do so much more, such as gripping or dealing multiple items at once, the point here is that it's awkward and clunky to deal cards or chuck dice this way, whereas if you were sat at a table you'd just grab the stuff with an effortless motion. Anyway, this is just my 2 cents to make buyers more wary of what they're actually getting before they purchase.TL; DR = It's MUCH easier to play an actual board game than it will ever be to use this."
