,Recommended,286160,31506836,Posted: 2 May,all,Virtual Volcano,"Tabletop simulator allows you to play board games with your friends, be it as simple as chest or something that another user created and shared on the work shop. It has vr compatibility which is a great feature that I sadly don't have the privilege to use.  I have invested about 9 hours in this game where 2 hours was spent trouble shooting my connection problems, at the end I figured that the only solution is to spam the connect button and pray you don't time out or the host decides to reset anything.Despite the connection issues I encountered I also ran into a problem where it would not allow me to host my own server but after spamming the button a few times it eventually allowed me to create a lobby.Where this game shines is in multiplayer, Tabletop simulator gives players a diverse arsenal of tools and ways to interact with objects on the board, this allows for some unforgettable moments and great laughs.Luckily if you don't have friends and you are willing to endure some spam you can browser servers and see what games are being played, how many players are currently playing in that lobby and whether or not the room is password protected, but the server browser is also not perfect because every time I use the filter option it seems to have no effect on the results given to me.so to summarizePros- Allows for very interactive gameplay- Great with friends- Huge selection of board games on the workshop- Host tools to change permission are plentiful and useful but not to a point where it becomes annoyingCons- Server browser filter seems to work some times- Players often crash when the game is reset- Controls are hard to get use too*Note : I have had more connection problems than I would find acceptable endure, I am not listing this because of my internet but it is something to take into consideration"
