,Recommended,286160,31768394,Posted: 15 May,all,Devistater,"Awesome ""game"" ! If you like board games, and playing them online (works great with people across the country), this is the game for you! This is basically a board game framework. Most of the games you get are just the pieces, like in real life, you still need to learn rules and setup and play game. This is not like getting Ticket to Ride on steam where it handles the entire gameplay for you, you just are making decisions on what to do. That being said, if you do the tutorial, there's tons of fun to be had! There's some decent paid DLC, and tons of great workshop content. My choices for good DLC would be Scythe, Vitaculture, Zombicide, and Cosmic Encounter. For workshop, sky is the limit! I've seen Risk Legacy, Battlestar Galactica, Pandemic and Pandemic Legacy, Settlers of Catan, Betrayal at House on the Hill, Dominion, Dead of Winter, Agricola, Caverna, Carcassonne, Mansions of Madness (haven't tried this but it would probably work great with the helper app), tons of D&D type games, and fan projects like Fallout Risk, etc. I especially like the ones that have scripts in them to help play, for instance the Forbidden Island with scripts to properly do the flood deck when you draw and shuffle. System requirements are very low, and probably would work on most low end laptops with intel integrated chips too. Voice chat is highly recommended, or even skype if you know the person. If you don't know if this is for you, check out the videos or youtube. For me, it's tons of fun and yesterday I got to play a round of Pandemic Legacy with a good friend who lives on the other side of the country that I don't get to see often enough."
