,Recommended,286160,32100036,Posted: 31 May,all,Apexecutioner,"I absolutely LOVE this game! Tabletop Simulator has great rendering, fantastic physics, and I found the controls to be pretty intuitive. The ""bread and butter"" of Tabletop Simulator, of course, is a combination of the Steam Workshop, and the ability to make your own games. With the Steam Workshop, people can easily make mods for all kinds of games - Monopoly, Splendor, D&D, Magic, Pokemon, Munchkin, Catan, and Dominion to name just a few. With just a few clicks, you can load up a game of Monopoly in a number of seconds and play in a virtual environment.I also adore the ability to design your own games. Once you get the hang of things, importing your own cards is easy and fun to do. I find Tabletop Simulator to be a perfect resource for playtesting my tabletop games without having to spend money on Game Crafter on physical cards and pieces. So if you're a game designer like me, this game can actually save you lots of money in playtesting! Yes, it's not the same as holding physical cards and playing with actual pieces, but it's a potential money-saver, so it's a give-and-take.I highly recommend this game for anyone who enjoys playing tabletop games, anything from Cards Against Humanity to Agricola and everything in between. As many reviewers have said in videos on YouTube, ""The possibilities are endless!"""
