,Not Recommended,286160,24274108,"Posted: 12 July, 2016",all,"M, the Cleaner <<Omega>>","For all it's cracked up to be, Tabletop Simulator as a game isn't actually that bad. Unlike other games which only offer one thing, this one offers what is essentially an infinite sandbox mode with the ability to create and/or play any game to your heart's desire.Despite this, there are two things holding it back and making it not worth buying. The community is in a weird state in which few people are actively on (I only really saw about 15 games going on at once) and the ones on being quite toxic (they will literally ban you from their games if you don't cater to their specific ""needs""). With this, you'll often be struggling to actively play games despite tts' main ""niche"" being that.Ultimately, it's really hard to find a reason to get this game unless you have a specific group of buddies to play it with. Until the community changes and is willing to be less obnoxious, the playerbase is just going to continue to die off."
