,Recommended,286160,35493163,Posted: 5 October,all,Dumbdave7,"Theres very little to say about this game. It's designed as a simulator for games played at a traditional tabletop. It's well done with controls that are a little difficult but not overly complicated. While i reccomend this game you will need a few things to make it truely worth it:1) you need to have other friends that own this game. While community servers can be fun in thier own right, if you want to truely enjoy the game. You'll need a bunch of your friends to play with you.2) you'll need to use the community workshop. While you have a small selection of games in the default package, the majority of what makes this game shine are the community submissions. If you know a board game, it's likely someone has made a mod for it. If you've seen it on Geek and Sundry's Tabletop, Its probably got a mod for it or will have one soon.3) you'll want to turn off the music when you start the game. I mean seriously, that music is worse than an elevator. Turn that stuff off.finally looking at some of the other reviews i've noticed some people are having connection problems and lag making the game unplayable. While i've not experience this issue be sure to test the connection within the first few hours to ensure you can get a steam refund if you do experience this problem."
